Hey everyone, We’re lost…we’re running a REV Spark MAX with a Through-Bore Encoder on our elevator mechanism, but we’re having some weird issues with the encoders.

The absolute encoder (m_absoluteEncoder.getPosition()) gives values, but they repeat periodically, so we can’t use it for setting positions.

The relative encoder (m_relativeEncoder.getPosition()) is always stuck at 0, no matter what we do.

We need to set the elevator to a certain position and in order to do that, we need encoder values to set it to. Since the relative is stuck at zero and the absolute is repeating values, we can’t do that. Please help us get the encoder values.

What we’ve tried:

Set the encoder to alternate on REV Hardware Client

Double Checked wiring

All firmware is updated

Changed the spark max and motor

Questions:

How can we code absolute encoders to set to a specific position?

Why is the relative encoder always reading 0?

Does the Through-Bore Encoder default to absolute mode, and if so, how do we switch it?

